[{"sha":"cec72d0e28c8a6172b2f041d319f062883e06ade","author":{"name":"A. Unique TensorFlower","email":"746aced590a184ef4169166e753f7c211e32e5fc@tensorflow.org"},"message":"Add bias adjustments when the scale for the bias would cause overflow.

In full-integer quantization, bias_scale is determined as input_scale * filter_scale. When the two dependent scales are too small, the INT32 quantized bias values will overflow and break the model. This change is to introduce a logic implemented in TOCO quantizer to MLIR's QuantizationDriver.

Deleted temporary patch that used fixed threshold for this adjustment.

[{"sha":"3994a7305c8afc3c7342b9733a3e99fc3da900f3","author":{"name":"Taehee Jeong","email":"9658aeb0d6dabc12b71efd5872bbf9f3c41b726b@google.com"},"message":"Add bias adjustments when the scale for the bias would cause overflow.
